<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-249-020  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 249 020.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Digital Review  May 8 1989 v6 n18 p27(2)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Ziff-Davis Publishing Co. 1989.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Sybase update handles text, image data types. (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Ballou, Melinda-Carol.andM;</AUTHOR><SUMMARY>Sybase has upgraded its relational database management system tosupport large documents and image data.andP;  Users will be able tointegrate large objects with other information, such as medicalimagery, engineering drawings, or forms which require a signature.andO;A data value or field as large as 2Gbytes can now be manipulatedby the system.andP;  There is also a configurable memory cache and apattern-matching feature for search and retrieval of data.andP;  Thenew features are included in the Sybase system's maintenance fees.andO;The system ranges in price from $10,000 to $100,000 depending uponthe CPU.andM;</SUMMARY><DESCRIPT>Company:   Sybase Inc. (product introduction).andO;Product:   Sybase (Data base management system) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Image ProcessingDocument Management SystemsData Base Management SystemsUpgrading.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Sybase Update Handles Text, Image Data TypesandM;EMERYVILLE, Calif.andP;  -- sybase has announced support for text and image datatypes in an upgrade to its relational database management system (RDBMS).andM;To handle these very long data strings, the Sybase system now providesstorage and manipulation capabilities of as much as 2GB for each data valueor field, the officials added.andP;  Each row in a table can now contain as manyas 250 text or image fields.andM;&quot;It really opens up yet another new world of applications that can be builtwith a database,&quot; said Rich Scheffer, Sybase's director of marketing.andM;&quot;They can manage everyting under the database, which makes it easier forusers to build their own applications in areas such as medical imaging(putting X-rays on line) and traditional engineering (putting drawingsdirectly into the database) or in businesses with claims forms or anythingthat requires a signature.&quot;andM;Imaging systems that are built on top of databases can be cumbersome,Scheffer said, but the ability to incorporate text and images into the SybaseRDBMS will provide performance improvements for users.andM;Rich Finkelstein, president of Performance Computing, a market researchcompany in Chicago, said that Sybase's integration of text and image datadifferentiates the company from other major relational database vendors.andM;&quot;Of the leading database vendors--DEC, Oracle and RelationalTechnology--Sybase is the first one to bring out this kind of support, and itwill be a while before the others do,&quot; Finkelstein said.andM;&quot;Text string support is one of the greatest problems facing databases today,&quot;Finkelstein said.andP;  &quot;People have very long documents that they need to storein databases ....andP;  [Now with Sybase] they can integrate documents with otherinformation--they don't want the document in one database and the supportinginformation in another, because it's very difficult to manipulate.&quot;andM;According to Scheffer, along with the ability to integrate very large objectsinto a data row, Sybase has built in navigational aids.andM;Text and image data can be accessed with standard SQL operators: &quot;select,&quot;&quot;insert,&quot; &quot;update,&quot; &quot;delete.&quot;andP;  Sybase's pattern-matching features provideadvanced search and retrieval capabilities and a configurable memory cachethat allows the system to move large blocks of data across the network fromserver to application.andM;Through a strategic relationship with Verity of Mountain view, Calif., adeveloper of intelligent full-text search and retrieval systems, sybasesupports more sophisticated text and image data access, officials said.andM;Scheffer said Sybase is working on providing support for multiprocessors:&quot;We're committed to it as a strategic direction, and we expect to have itwithin the year--but this is not a product announcement.&quot;andM;The new text and imaging support features are included as part of themaintenance fees charged for the Sybase system.andP;  Prices for the system rangefrom $10,000 to $100,000, depending on the CPU.andM;Sybase Inc. can be contacted at 6475 Christie Ave., Emeryville, CA 94608,(415 596-3500.andO;</TEXT></DOC>